article.headline: Winston-Salem 68, Lipscomb 58
article.story: AMES, Iowa (AP) -- Roy Peake scored 16 points and Brian Fisher hit four 3-point baskets while adding 14 points, leading Winston-Salem State to a 68-58 victory over Lipscomb on Saturday night. Isiah Tucker and Michael Puckett each scored 10 for Winston-Salem State (1-1), which went 14-for-26 from 3-point range to finish third in Iowa State's Cyclone Challenge. Devon Seaford and Eddie Ard led Lipscomb (0-2) with 12 points each. Jason Hopkins grabbed 12 rebounds to go with five points for the Bisons. Winston-Salem State jumped to a 13-2 lead, fell behind 37-29 early in the second half, then hit seven 3s during a 6 1/2-minute stretch while building a 55-47 lead. Hopkins' three-point play drew Lipscomb to 56-53, but Winston-Salem State answered with a 7-0 run that included two baskets by Peake to regain control.
